    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<head>Jim to Paul <date value="1916-11-15">Nov 15th [1916]</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1916-11-15">Nov 15th [1916]</date></dateline>
            
            <salute>Dear Paul:</salute>
        		</opener>
        		
        		<p>
            This is some climate &mdash; Mist
            and rain most of the time.  I have
            no machine as yet but haven’t missed
            anything.
            </p><p>
            Thanks for sending the World’s 
            Work.  A bunch came.  Capt. T. is
            at <unclear>Cazean [sp?]</unclear> but I’ll ask him about
            the pictures when he gets back.  Also
            I’ll remind “Skip” to send you the
            news.  He’s one fine boy and has
            been mighty nice to me.
            </p><p>
            I have Bill’s bunk in the shed
            with “Havi”.
            </p><p>
            We all motored over and saw
            a Tank the other day.  Very interesting.
            Some British officers coming to eat 
            with us to morrow.
            </p><p>
            Lots of my old friends have gone
            since I was at the front last.
            </p><p>
            Boches come over on clear
            nights and drop bombs.  Pretty 
            close last time.  Skip is to try
                        
            <pb n="[p.2]"/>
            
            night flying in Nieuport.  A couple
            of Frenchmen here do it when
            there’s a moon.
            </p><p>
            I feel on the bum for fair 
            in this climate.
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <salute>Well old boy &mdash; here’s to
            good luck to you.</salute>
            
            <signed>Jim.</signed>
        		</closer>
        		
            <!-- [There is no envelope with this letter.] -->
            
            </div1>
        </body>
